title: Correspondence regarding the American Statistical Association, 1840-1844
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: This collection of letters (1840-1844) contains the initial responses for those invited to join the recently inaugurated American Statistical Association. The respondents include well-known statisticians such as Edward Jarvis, Francis Lieber, J.M. Peck, and William Prescott. The initial letter, written by ASA Secretary Joseph B. Felt, was sent (along with the constitution and by-laws) to nominated individuals after the ASA organizing meeting held in November 1839. These letters were used in an exhibit for the ASA Sesquicentennial in 1989.

title: Organization and proceedings of the American Statistical Association, 1839-1872
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Disbound volume, titled "Organization & Proceedings of the American Statistical Association, 1839-1872," contains the handwritten records concerning the creation of the Association, the constitution and by-laws, meeting minutes and proceedings, names of the Society's Fellows, names of Honorary, Corresponding, and Foreign members, and account information.
